1. Depth First Search (Brute Force) : T.C. - O(N^2), S.C. - O(N)

Approach: Apart from dfs function, we have created a getMax function that will return root.val + max(left node, right node).
That will help how?
For every node, we will now the node with the max value of left and right side (with max values). For ex - 
        -10
       /   \
     9     20
          /   \
         15    7
In this case, one possible maxPath solution is -10->20->15 which gives 34
I was confused with how to call a recursive call for tree nodes, so always use dfs internal function.
Here every node is visited twice ~ O(N^2)

class Solution:
    def maxPathSum(self, root: Optional[TreeNode]) -> int:
        
        res = -float('inf')

        def dfs(root):

            nonlocal res

            if not root:
                return None
            left = self.getMax(root.left)
            right = self.getMax(root.right)
            res = max(res, root.val + left + right)
            dfs(root.left)
            dfs(root.right)
        dfs(root)
        return res

    def getMax(self, root: Optional[TreeNode]) -> int:
        
        if not root:
            return 0

        left = self.getMax(root.left)
        right = self.getMax(root.right)

        path = root.val + max(left,right)
        return max(0,path)
